result.execSummary:
The defendant Nichole A Wilke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

11:54 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court has received the PSI and recommendation along with two letters.  State has received a copy of the PSI and defense recommendation with no corrections, additions or deletions.  Atty Privat has received a copy of the PSI and defense recommendation with no corrections, additions or deletions.  Statement by Cindy Gozinski.  Statement by Virgie Anzivino.  Sentencing argument by ADA.  Sentencing argument by Atty Privat.

Court sentences the defendant to:

18 months initial confinement and 24 months of Extended Supervision

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:

-Defendant is to maintain absolute sobriety - not to possess or consume any alcohol, illegal drugs or prescription drugs without a valid prescription.
-Find and maintain employment.
-Continue to take prescribed mediation as prescribed.
-Defendant is not to be in possession of any illegals drugs, prescription medications that do not belong to the defendant or drug paraphernalia.
-Court costs.
-No Contact with Lorna Otto and Cindy Gozinski.
-Letter of apology to the victims.
-DNA sample
-Defendant is not to be in possession of any firearms or ammunition.
-Court leaves it up to the agent the best possible treatment when released from prison.

Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance abuse Program.

Court remands the defendant to the custody of the Green Lake County Sheriffs Department.

Court adjourned at 12:15 p.m.

Sentencing hearing on November 11, 2014 at 02:00 pm.

1:51 p.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present with Attorney Barb Privat.

ADA recites agreement - defendant will plea, as charged - requesting a PSI.  Attorney Privat and the defendant concur.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - waived.  Court goes over the elements of the offense.  Court instructs regarding the maximum penalties.  Court instructs regarding deportation.  Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.  

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently, and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty and orders a judgment of conviction be entered today.  Court orders a Presentence Investigation be completed and done within sixty days - argued sentencing to be scheduled thereafter.

Court adjourned at 1:57 p.m.
Status hearing on August 26, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

2:44 p.m.  State by ADA Lisa Vanden Branden.  Defendant present with Attorney Barbara Privat.

Statement by Attorney Privat - defendant will be waiving her right to a preliminary hearing - defendant concurs.  Court instructs defendant of her right to a preliminary hearing - defendant waives this right - court accepts the waiver and binds the defendant over for trial.

ADA files an Information with the court and provides a copy to Attorney Privat.  Attorney Privat confirms receipt of the Information and waives reading.  Court makes statement regarding the maximum penalties.  Attorney Privat enters a plea of NOT GUILTY on behalf of the defendant.

Status Hearing to be held in approximately thirty days.

Court adjourned at 2:47 p.m.
